On August 31, 2020 USDA announced the continuation of the Seamless Summer Option for school districts, which will allow the District to offer breakfast and lunch at no charge to all students enrolled at Indiana Area School District through December 31, 2020. This means that regardless of your students' free/reduced or paid status, they will be eligible for a free breakfast and lunch.

Students who are learning remotely or not scheduled to attend in person on certain days will have the option to pick up meals every Wednesday at the Senior High School for those days (and only those days) that they are not scheduled to be in person in the schools. Parents can reserve meals, by visiting the District's website and filling out the survey on the Food Service page. This week's survey will close at 3:15 p.m. today

IHS Welcomes Incoming Freshmen and New IHS Upperclassmen!

IHS held it's annual INCOMING FRESHMEN ORIENTATION via a "split schedule" of morning and afternoon sessions in order to meet safety and social distancing protocols established for IHS and IASD for the start of the upcoming 2020-21 school year.

The purpose of the orientation was to allow incoming Freshmen, as well as upperclassmen that are new to IHS, the opportunity to meet the wonderful and caring faculty, staff, and administrators at IHS; to acclimate themselves to the layout and health safety arrangements made to the Senior High building; to run through their daily schedule in an abbreviated format and; to receive their IASD supplied 1:1 Chromebook devices for student success inside and outside the classroom and school environment.

Students were welcomed to IHS by Mr. Wade McElheny, IHS Principal, and Mr. Doug Johnson, IHS Assistant Principal followed by tours of IHS provided by homeroom teachers.

Special assistance for the orientation was provided by the IHS Ambassadors under the guidance of Mr. Matt Neil.

post_text: Parent Communication Regarding Selected Learning Option - We have developed this plan for instruction for students through November 6th to give you and our students and families stability. In order to operate effectively, we have to finalize our class rosters and family selections. We have been very flexible in allowing families to contact their child’s school to discuss the options available and address any concerns or questions that exist. At this point, in order to be ready for the start of the school year, we respectfully ask that you understand that we will not be making any changes to selections at the current time. If something arises and you feel your circumstances are unique, please contact your child’s principal to discuss what can be done. http://edl.io/n1284765

post_text: The Indiana Area School District has an anticipated vacancy for a full-time Assistant Business Manager. Must have a four-year degree in Business Administration specializing in accounting. Three years of auditing and/or accounting experience in a governmental or non-profit setting is preferred. Requires proficiency in MS Office. Responsibilities include accounting, internal auditing, cash management, investments, student activity funds and fixed asset accounting. Enrollment of approximately 2800 students with a $56 million budget. Benefits included. To apply, please submit a letter of interest along with a resume to Jared Cronauer, Business Manager, Indiana Area School District, 501 East Pike, Indiana, PA 15701. Applications received by July 31, 2020 are assured a review. Clearances will be required prior to start. EOE.

Interested in twirling a baton? Spinning a flag? Dancing in a kickline? The IHS Visual Ensemble with the IHS Marching Band, is now opening registration to students grades 8 – 12.

The IHS Visual Ensemble uses a variety of show equipment in Majorettes, I-ettes, and Colorguard during performances at football games, parades, and local events. We work with batons, different flags, and dance/drill team styles. No experience is necessary.

The ability to complete a double pirouette, leap, and eye-high kicks are beneficial for Dance.

Registration can be found on the IHS Facebook marching band page or by contacting Mr. Olear at jolear@iasd.cc

IASD is PROUD to share the following message from the Indiana Free Library:

Even though our Indiana Free Library building is closed to patrons for your safety, the IFL Children’s Department has many fun activities planned for this special summer. You will still be able to find great books to take part in these wonderful annual events. We'll help you find out how! Prizes are involved for our young readers that read and take part in the many fun things we have planned.

Monday's are for the small ones, birth - 3 years of age and are named the Fablers.
Tuesday's are for kids aged 4-6 and they are called the Bards.
Wednesday's are for our oldest Storytellers at ages 7-12.
Thursday's are Summer School at Hogwarts for our teens.

Please follow this link for more information and to register for our Summer Reading Program!
https://indianafreelibrary.org/what-we-do/youth-programs/2020-summer-reading-program.html?fbclid=IwAR2IvovSzdGQnHkopbPdDiwkvbGC_oh3QrA857SDm2YKjJSmnRZvXXsPPmg

Reminder: Summer meal distribution has been changed to five (5) days' worth of meals being distributed once per week. Meals are distributed on Tuesdays at the Indiana Area Senior High School location from 9:00 a.m - 11:00 a.m.. Families MUST pre-order for two weeks at a time. The deadline for meals on June 16 and June 23 has passed, but it's not too late to order for June 30 and July 7. For June 30 and July 7 pickup, you MUST pre-order NO LATER THAN 3:00 p.m. on Thursday, June 18 in order to participate. This will enable us to prepare enough meals. Parents no longer have to bring their child(ren) with them, but they must name the children who will be receiving meals and also indicate if someone else will be picking up meals on their behalf. Please pre-order at the following link:

https://forms.gle/8fewToZqWg4wvqBX6

If you have questions, contact Holly at hhartman@iasd.cc.

post_text:
Important Information about Summer Meals: The current school year meal distribution is ending June 12, 2020. Beginning the following week, breakfasts and lunches (Monday - Friday) will be distributed every Tuesday, with June 16th being the first distribution day. Five (5) days' worth of meals will be distributed to students once per week at the Senior High School location only on TUESDAYS from 9:00 a.m. to 11:00 a.m.

Families MUST pre-order for two weeks at a time. For June 16 and June 23, you MUST pre-order NO LATER THAN 3:00 p.m. on Thursday, June 4 in order to participate. This will enable us to prepare enough meals and also means parents will no longer have to bring their child(ren) with them at the time of pick-up. Please pre-order at the following link:

https://forms.gle/AVVBEXmaxBvewY159

Be sure to watch for information on the following two weeks' ordering, which will be for June 30 and July 7. The current order form covers only June 16 and June 23.

If you have questions, contact Holly Hartman at hhartman@iasd.cc.

ATTENTION IHS SENIORS: The School Counseling Office at the senior high school is thrilled with the information we have received from you about the scholarships and awards you have earned from your various schools and community organizations, and we are so proud of all your hard work!

Just a reminder that all information regarding any scholarships/awards you have received, must be emailed to Mrs. Smyers (csmyers@iasd.cc) or Mrs. Smith (ksmith@iasd.cc) no later than FRIDAY, MAY 15, 2020 at 4:00 p.m. We must have your information by the deadline in order for you to be recognized at the Virtual Senior Awards Ceremony on May 27th. Please keep an eye out for the invitation that will be coming your way!

IHS Instrumental Music Department would like to congratulate IHS Sophomores Carly Wang and Victor Wu for advancing to the 2020 PMEA All-State Orchestra level!

Carly Wang received 7th chair, Violin 1 and Victor Wu received 8th chair, Violin 1 which would have made the two music students stand partners! In addition, both are 10th graders, so this is a wonderful achievement for these students!

Video auditions were held for Western Regional Orchestra (Regionals) that determined seating and advancement to All-State Orchestra which although cancelled will still be considered an official PMEA event.

The Statewide Support & Referral Helpline is staffed by skilled and compassionate staff that are available 24/7 to respond to those struggling with anxiety and other challenging emotions due to the COVID-19 emergency. Staff at the Helpline refer callers to community-based resources that can further help to meet individual needs.

The toll-free, round-the-clock support line is officially operational. The number to call is 1-855-284-2494. For TTY, dial 724-631-5600.

In an effort to better serve our District families during this difficult time, we are adding another distribution location for student meals. Starting on Monday, March 30, meals will also be distributed at the Shelocta Community Presbyterian Church in Shelocta from 11:00 a.m. to 12:00 p.m., Monday thru Friday. To ensure that the District will have enough meals available at this location, we are asking that parents or guardians email Holly Hartman at hhartman@iasd.cc or call (724) 463-8713 to let us know the students for whom you will be picking up and the days you will be participating. Please let us know by Friday, March 27th at 12:00 pm. We thank you in advance and look forward to working with you.

This District will also continue to operate meal distribution at Ben Franklin Elementary and the Senior High School, Monday thru Friday, from 11:00 a.m. to 1:00 p.m. Parents are encouraged to have students present when picking up meals.

We welcome all IASD families to take advantage of this service during the District shutdown.

post_text: Indiana Area School District will continue to serve meals from 11:00 a.m. to 1:00 p.m. Monday through Friday while our school buildings remain closed. The current two locations are Ben Franklin and the Senior High School. The District is working on adding a distribution site in Shelocta. The details of this possible location will be released shortly. All meals served by the District are free to children ages 2-18 regardless of household income. Children should be with their parents/guardians at the time of pickup. Meals will be served in a drive-thru fashion near the front doors of both schools. Lunch and a breakfast meal will be given to each student simultaneously.

Dear families,

We have started to use the School News app by Edlio, an activity feed for consuming alerts, news, and events for participating schools. It’s a simple way to view the school’s news feeds and calendars, and also receive push notifications directly from us.

It’s free to download to your iOS or Android phone and quick to set up:
1. Go to the App Store or Google Play and search for “School News by Edlio” to install.

2. Open the app and search for the school; tap “Add School.” If you have kids in other Edlio-powered schools, add them to the app too. We are asking that you select Indiana Area School District as their school since that is where the most pertinent news is released.

3. Enable push notification by going to the Alerts tab and tapping “Enable Notifications.”

All of the news and events posted to our website are posted here for easy access. You can also add multiple Edlio-powered schools to gather all news, events, and alerts in this one app. We’ll send push notifications out to keep you updated on urgent news.

post_text:
Congratulations to IHS Science Club!

On Saturday, February 22, the IHS Science Club sent students to Slippery Rock University to compete in the Region Nine Pennsylvania Junior Academy of Science fair.

These students created and presented projects in various categories. Thirty-five students earned first place awards, thus advancing to the state level competition at Penn State University this May.

Special Awards were presented to Paige Mitsko, George Zhang, Yahya Farag, Amelia Kuzneski, Melanie Navaratna, Muneeb Kasi, and Emma Grim recognizing them as best in their categories.

In addition, congratulations to Olivia Krimin, who earned a perfect score in the Chemistry category, Eliza Ray, who was awarded with the Charles “Chick” Stewart Senior High Science Award, and Julian Yerger, who earned the Innovation Award.

Congratulations to all who competed!
